[{"incoming_email": "Can I get invoice from 2025 and also where do I find API docs and also why my login failed once yesterday?", "similarity": 0.4215485453605652, "intent": "Random Miscellaneous"}, {"incoming_email": "Hey, I'm building an integration using the CloudSync API and keep getting a 401 Unauthorized on POST /v1/files/upload even though I generated a fresh access token from the developer dashboard 10 minutes ago. Here's the response:

{"error":"invalid_token","request_id":"req_44210x"}

Any idea what's going on? Also, is there a rate limit I should know about for bulk uploads?", "similarity": 0.3800714910030365, "intent": "API & Developer Support"}, {"incoming_email": "Hi there, I'd like to set up two-factor authentication on my account for extra security. Could you walk me through the steps? Thanks in advance!", "similarity": 0.2931269109249115, "intent": "How-To"}]

[{"incoming_email": "Hey, I'm building an integration using the CloudSync API and keep getting a 401 Unauthorized on POST /v1/files/upload even though I generated a fresh access token from the developer dashboard 10 minutes ago. Here's the response:

{"error":"invalid_token","request_id":"req_44210x"}

Any idea what's going on? Also, is there a rate limit I should know about for bulk uploads?", "similarity": 0.4975765645503998, "intent": "API & Developer Support"}, {"incoming_email": "Sign in with Google keeps bouncing back to login page. Chrome on Windows 10. One-time saw 401 invalid_client.", "similarity": 0.41944023966789246, "intent": "Authentication"}, {"incoming_email": "We're building an internal automation on top of the CloudSync API and noticed webhooks are only available at the account level, not per-folder. This means we get flooded with events for folders we don't care about. Any plans to support folder-scoped webhook subscriptions? This would significantly reduce our processing overhead.", "similarity": 0.39010417461395264, "intent": "API & Developer Support"}]
